author: Leou Chen, Phil Helsel
title: Wuhan, where COVID-19 epidemic began, raises death toll by 1,290
description: The government of the Chinese city of Wuhan revised its death toll with an additional 1,290, bringing the total there to 3,869. State media said the change is because some died at home, as well as misreporting in amid the epidemic.
content:
Wuhan, where COVID-19 epidemic began, raises death toll by 1,290
The government in the Chinese city of Wuhan added 1,290 people to its COVID-19 death toll, bringing the number of deaths there now to 3,869.
